    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 standard configuration and the model influence rating is Medium, consistent with the risk-informed acceptance framework. All quantitative validation metrics satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds. The material property dataset used as model input predates the model revision date by approximately three weeks; the responsible analyst documented a judgment that the revision (contact stiffness and thread mesh updates) was not material to the applicability of the material property characterization data. This judgment was not independently reviewed and no formal re-validation was conducted against the revised model configuration. The assessment team accepted this gap under the overall Medium assurance level.",
